                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nVasopressin therapy causes vasoconstriction, and side and adverse effects include myocardial ischemia, which may be evident by the client's complaints of chest pain. Elevated temperature, bounding peripheral pulses, and a BUN of 20 mg/dL (7.1 mmol/L) are not adverse effects. Vasopressin therapy can cause hypothermia. Because vasopressin has potent vasoconstrictive effects on the peripheral arterioles, weak versus bounding pulses may be found. The normal BUN is 10 to 20 mg/dL (3.6 to 7.1 mmol/L).\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, a side or adverse effect of vasopressin. Use knowledge of the adverse effects of vasopressin therapy to answer this question. Because vasopressin therapy can cause hypothermia and acute kidney injury, options 3 and 4 (normal values for BUN) can be immediately eliminated. Because vasopressin has potent vasoconstrictive effects on the peripheral arterioles, weak versus bounding pulses may be found, so option 2 can be eliminated.",
