                        "content": "An 8-year-old child is being treated with desmopressin. Understanding the purpose of this medication, the nurse would set which goal for this child?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nDesmopressin may be used to treat nocturnal enuresis; therefore, the goal for the child will be several nights in sequence without enuresis. The medication does not increase urine output and does not have an effect on white blood cells. The medication is not indicated as an intervention in the child with asthma.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, a goal for the child receiving desmopressin. Focus on the child's age. Remembering that desmopressin is used to treat nocturnal enuresis will lead you to option 1. All of the goals are appropriate goals, but only the one related to enuresis is appropriate for this child.",
