                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client with diabetes insipidus asks the nurse about the purpose of a new medication, vasopressin. The nurse provides teaching about the medication. Which statement by the client indicates successful teaching?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nVasopressin is a vasopressor and an antidiuretic. It increases reabsorption of water by the renal tubules, resulting in a decreased urinary flow rate. It also directly stimulates contraction of smooth muscle, causing vasoconstriction and stimulating peristalsis.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nEliminate options 1 and 4 first because they are comparable or alike and relate to decreasing muscle contractions. Regarding the remaining options, recall the pathophysiology of diabetes insipidus to direct you to the correct option.",
